Johann Lonfat (born 11 September 1973 in Martigny) is a Swiss footballer. A midfielder, he is currently without a club.
==Career==
During his career, Lonfat represented Lausanne Sports (1991-92), FC Sion (1992-98), Servette FC (1998-2002 and 2007-09) and FC Sochaux (2002-2007, playing 96 "Ligue 1" matches with one goal), subsequently returning to Servette. A Swiss international, he received a total of 24 caps.
